                                <p>
                                    The day of your earlobe repair procedure, your TOPS plastic surgeon will meet you in 
                                    procedure room to go over any last minute questions or concerns you may have. Your 
                                    Houston plastic surgeon may make some preoperative markings, and will perform extensive 
                                    checks and attention to detail ensuring high quality care and safety. This procedure is 
                                    completed under local anesthesia.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    During the procedure, our Houston plastic surgeons pay meticulous attention to detail and 
                                    work as a team to ensure a great result with a focus on safety and quality. Your family 
                                    will be updated of your status periodically. Correction of earlobe usually takes our 
                                    Houston plastic surgeons 30 to 40 minutes to complete. Please keep in mind that the 
                                    cosmetic procedure may take a little longer for the surgical set up and for our patients 
                                    to fully recover in the post-operative care unit.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6 " id="section-recovery-expect">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>
                                    What can you expect for recovery after an Earlobe Repair at The Oaks Plastic Surgery in
                                    Houston, Texas?
                                </h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    After your earlobe repair in Houston, Texas, you will have a dressing around your earlobe.
                                    You will be instructed to place antibiotic ointment on the incision twice a day. You may 
                                    shower the day of the procedure, allowing soap and water to run over your wounds without 
                                    rubbing or scrubbing any of the surgical areas. You will be advised to cover the incision 
                                    with a bandaid over the ears for six weeks following the procedure in order to decrease the 
                                    risk of trauma. You will be advised to refrain from heavy activity or sports for six weeks 
                                    during the healing process.
                                </p>
                            </div>
